rounds.response:
I've evaluated your offer and cannot accept it because the value exchange doesn't work in my favor. You're offering 5 Wood (which I value at 9 each, totaling 45) and 5 Wheat (valued at 5 each, totaling 25), summing to 70 value units for me. In return, you're asking for 3 Brick (27 each, totaling 81) and 2 Ore (32 each, totaling 64), which sums to 145 value units from my inventory. This results in a net loss of 75 value units for me.

I propose a different trade: I'll offer 1 Ore (high value for me) in exchange for 10 Wood and 10 Wheat. This allows me to part with a resource I have in surplus (14 Ore) while gaining bulk lower-value resources that you seem more willing to trade. This gives me a net value gain of 108 based on my valuation system, making it a fairer exchange.

[Offer: 1 Ore -> 10 Wood, 10 Wheat]
